Interface IAtomContainer

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cloneable, ICDKObject, IChemObject, IChemObjectListener
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IAminoAcid, IBioPolymer, ICrystal, IMolecule, IMonomer, IPDBMonomer, IPDBPolymer, IPolymer, IQueryAtomContainer, IRing, IStrand
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AminoAcid, AtomContainer, BioPolymer, ChargeGroup, Crystal, DebugAminoAcid, DebugAtomContainer, DebugBioPolymer, DebugCrystal, DebugMolecule, DebugMonomer, DebugPDBMonomer, DebugPDBPolymer, DebugPolymer, DebugRing, DebugStrand, MDMolecule, Molecule, Monomer, NNAminoAcid, NNAtomContainer, NNBioPolymer, NNCrystal, NNMolecule, NNMonomer, NNPDBMonomer, NNPDBPolymer, NNPolymer, NNRing, NNStrand, PDBMonomer, PDBPolymer, PDBStrand, PharmacophoreQuery, Polymer, QueryAtomContainer, Residue, Ring, Strand

    public interface IAtomContainer
extends IChemObject, IChemObjectListener
    Base class for all chemical objects that maintain a list of Atoms and ElectronContainers.

    Looping over all IBonds in the IAtomContainer is typically done like: 

      for (IBond bond : atomContainer.bonds()) {
    // do something
  }
    If you do need an explicit Iterator then use 
     Iterator bondIter = atomContainer.bonds().iterator();

    steinbeck
    Created on:
